<h3 id="computational-ciphers-and-semantic-security">Computational ciphers and semantic security</h3>

<p>For perfect security, the only way to achieve perfect security is to have keys that are as long as messages. However this is impractical. The way we shall od this is to considerr not all possible advarsaries, but only <em>computational feasible</em> adversaries, that is the â€œreal worldâ€ adversaries must perform their calculations on read computers using a resonable amount of time and monery.</p>

<p>This leads to a weaker security model: <strong>â€œsemantic securityâ€</strong></p>
